-- Absa, Afgri, Standard Bank May Move: South African Equity Market Preview
-- Mike Cohen
-- 2010-06-23T05:38:07Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-22/absa-afgri-standard-bank-may-move-south-african-equity-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following stocks may rise or
fall in  South Africa . Symbols are in parentheses and prices are
from the last close.  
 The  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  fell the most in more
than a week, declining 111.82, or 0.4 percent, to 27,917.51.  
 Absa Group Ltd.  (ASA SJ): A government report today will
probably show South African inflation eased in May to 4.6
percent on an annual basis from 4.8 percent in April, according
to the median estimate of economists surveyed by Bloomberg.  
 Absa, South Africa’s largest retail bank, rose 1.86 rand,
or 1.5 percent, to 128.51 rand.  Standard Bank Group Ltd.  (SBK
SJ), Africa’s biggest lender, gained 1.59 rand, or 1.5 percent,
to 107.84 rand.  
 Afgri Ltd.  (AFR SJ): South African Grain Information
Service releases corn-stocks monthly data. Afgri, which
produces, trades and stores agricultural products, declined 12
cents, or 1.9 percent, to 6.23 rand.  
 Shares or American depositary receipts of the following
South African companies closed as follows:  
 Anglo American Plc (AAUKY US) fell 1.4 percent to $19.55.
AngloGold Ashanti Ltd. (AU US) dropped 0.2 percent to $43.68.
BHP Billiton Plc (BBL US) slipped 2 percent to $57.77. DRDGold
Ltd. (DROOY US) declined 2.8 percent to $4.52. Gold Fields Ltd.
(GFI US) retreated 1.4 percent to $13.40. Harmony Gold Mining
Co. (HMY US) gained 0.9 percent to $10.23. Impala Platinum
Holdings Ltd. (IMPUY US) dropped 2.5 percent to $25.31. Sappi
Ltd. (SPP US) slid 1.2 percent to $3.99. Sasol Ltd. (SSL US)
decreased 2.8 percent to $37.70. Telkom South Africa Ltd. (TLKGY
US) rose 2.5 percent to $20.61.  
